payload.text:
Fix iOS Safari top extra gap (final reliable fix):

1) In <head> keep:
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover, maximum-scale=1">

2) Force page to start at absolute top (no safe-area padding on body):
html, body { margin:0; padding:0; height:100%; overflow:hidden; }

3) Add JS that sets a CSS variable based on window.innerHeight (Safari-safe):
- On load + resize + orientationchange:
  document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--app-h', `${window.innerHeight}px`);

4) Use that variable for the OUTER wrapper that owns the background (NOT 100vh):
.outer-wrap { height: var(--app-h); min-height: var(--app-h); position: fixed; inset: 0; }

5) Ensure the app shell is pinned to top inside the wrapper (no vertical centering that can introduce a top gap):
- If currently using align-items:center on the wrapper, change to:
  align-items: flex-start;
  justify-content: center;
- Give the app shell a top margin of 0:
  .app-shell { margin-top: 0; }

6) Safe-area usage:
- Do NOT apply env(safe-area-inset-top) to body/wrapper.
- Only apply it inside the header as padding-top if needed:
  .app-header { padding-top: env(safe-area-inset-top); }
  .content { padding-top: 0; }

Apply globally so the blue background and header start immediately with no empty space above in iOS Safari.
Output ONLY updated HTML.

